$interpreted: Strict Bear Elder: There have been humans trespassing in Totemtaff these past few days. We should act accordingly.
Impulsive Bear Elder: Yes, illegal miners... they must be Sunshine infantry in disguise. We should attack!
Impulsive Bear Elder: We have to show them whose land this is!
Crushfang: But ever since Dylan took control of the Sunshine infantry there's been an armistice. There's no proof these miners are from the Kingdom.
Crushfang: This is not a reason for war.
Impulsive Bear Elder: But...
Crushfang: Do not attack the Sunshine Infantry without my orders!
Dagger: Whose side are you on? You should be protecting the bears! Protecting Totemtaff!
Dagger: And what about all those who died for the sake of the Golems!?
Crushfang: Many bears have already lost their lives to war. I guess you'd like an even higher body count?
Dagger: Coward!

Dagger: Strange, doesn't look like they're mining... 
Are they... spies or something?
Illegal Miner Foreman: Bears! Run for it!
Dagger: Not so fast!
Dagger: Can't you just stay down!?
Illegal Miner Foreman: Kill him!
Crushfang: Dagger, look out!
Dagger: I don't need a weakling like you looking out for me!
Crushfang: Listen, I hate humans as much as you do, but I can't allow more bears to die in a pointless war.
Dagger: Whole lot of good you've done so far! My father's dead because of you!
Dagger: You have no right to lead the bears!
Strict Bear Elder: Dagger!
Dagger: Elder?
Strict Bear Elder: Everything the chieftain does, he does because he cares for you. Mind your attitude towards him.
Dagger: Everything he does, he does trying to make amends for my father's death!
Strict Bear Elder: Regardless, he does care for you.

Dagger: How come I never feel it then?
He always punishes me... keeps me from anything and everything.
Dagger: That's supposed to show me he cares!?
Strict Bear Elder: Your Rite of Passage is near. It's important to the chieftain, so don't embarrass yourself.
Dagger: Hmph...
